/a>, and several of you agree.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I always thinking why address bar on top? the half of screen is closed by your finger. and now it happened! Apple ftw, waiting this feature in google chrome</p>â€” Gerasimov Aleksey (@xAlekSayx) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/xAlekSayx/status/1444043675286261764?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-541268-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">October 1, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Yep love it. Iâ€™m<br />Not changing the address bar back.  Having it at the bottom of the screen makes complete sense.</p>â€” Dr. Simon Spence (@macinfoirl) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/macinfoirl/status/1444066289828384771?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-541268-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">October 1, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I really like the new Safari. Probably the best thing about iOS 15.</p>â€” Here's Pete (@Heres_pete) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/Heres_pete/status/1444061579926925313?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-541268-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">October 1, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/facebook-verma.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/10159385922251544&amp;xcust=1-1-541268-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>iPadÂ Pro on the horizontalÂ </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Reports suggest that Apple isÂ <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/538767/ipad-pro-rumor-landscape-camera-apple-logo.html\" target=\"_blank\">changing the iPad Proâ€™s default orientation to landscape</a>, which would involve changing the placement of the rear Apple logo and the front camera.Â You have strong opinions about this possible change.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>This is a dumb idea. Put in a second camera but donâ€™t force the landscape. There are plenty of things (documents, newspapers, magazinesâ€¦) that are much better viewed vertically</p>â€” El Merengue (@Elmerengue) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/Elmerengue/status/1441758607528366101?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-541268-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">September 25, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>What is this April Fools? I sincerely hope this rumour isnâ€™t true. Sounds like something ridiculous that Apple would say to flush out a â€œleakyâ€ employee. Whatâ€™s odd is why would this excite anyone â€“ just rotate the device!</p>â€” Joshua Van Buskirk (@JVB2112) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/JVB2112/status/1441754061645258752?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-541268-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">September 25, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Are use my iPad in landscape mode all the time. It makes sense to have a similar aspect ratio to your desktop. And it makes more sense for video recording.<br /><br />And there I go ruining my vacation by talking shop!</p>â€” Paul T. (@paulvt) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/paulvt/status/1441757644717535232?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-541268-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">September 25, 2021</a></blockquote></div></figure><div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/facebook-lunscher.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macwo